						               													<description>After the destruction of most of Manresa during the War of the Spanish Succession, the four main classes of the city start working to rebuild it: the bourgeois and the traders build a palace that will house the city hall, once the old ones affected by the 1713 fire are demolished; the artisans and the farmers rebuild the burnt houses from most of the city; the clerks request the manufacturing of a new altarpiece for the Seu (the city&amp;rsquo;s cathedral) because the old ones were burnt, and the bourbonic army strengthens the city&amp;rsquo;s defenses by fortifying the barracks in Puig Mercadal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a slightly asymmetrical worker placement, where players try to be the first to finish the three reconstruction phases of their buildings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, the players send the workers outside the city to the production placements; then some misfortunes could stop the production of resources (fires, droughts or collapses); after that the players gather their production (stone for the walls, salt to pay workers&amp;rsquo; and artisans&amp;rsquo; salaries, water to make mortar or wood for the scaffoldings); finally they use the resources to finish if possible one of the reconstruction phases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is an advanced variant adding a fourth reconstruction phase (the new banner of the city) and a different skill for each class.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
